Use the `/run` command to execute IdlerGear:

### Common Operations

```bash
# Load project context
/run idlergear context

# Create task
/run idlergear task create "Add authentication"

# List tasks
/run idlergear task list --preview --limit 10

# Capture note
/run idlergear note create "Decision: using JWT tokens instead of sessions"

# Check vision
/run idlergear vision show

# Close completed task
/run idlergear task close 123
```

